          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>State CHIP Flexibility Act of 2017</b></p> <p class="MsoNormal">This bill establishes an exception to the requirement that unused Children's Health Insurance Program (CHIP) allotments to states for FY2017 be reduced by one-third. A state shall&nbsp;receive the exception if: (1) the remaining allotment amounts are with respect to expenditures incurred during any quarter of FY2017, (2) the state submitted a claim under&nbsp;its child health plan after September 30, 2017 and before December 31, 2017, and (3) the state could have&nbsp;alternatively submitted a claim for federal funding under&nbsp;its state Medicaid program. </p><a name="summary"> </a>]]></text>
